    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2007-03-15</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in Senate</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2007-03-31T16:38:43Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Capital Gains Inflation Relief Act of 2007 - Amends the Internal Revenue Code to allow an inflation adjustment based upon the gross domestic product deflator to the adjusted basis of certain assets (including C corporation common stock and tangible property used in a trade or business) held by a taxpayer for more than three years for purposes of determining gain or loss on the sale or other disposition of such assets.</p><p>Sets forth rules for applying such inflation adjustment to short sales, regulated investment companies and real estate investment trusts, partnerships and other pass-thru entities, and dispositions of assets between related persons. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
